            "answer_text": "It\u2019s impossible to make a comparison because they aren\u2019t comparable countries, but pressed for an answer I would have to say China as the country has very good standards even in the most rural and poor areas. China also has more potential, whereas Japan is tapped out until they fix immigration. Look at a third country, the United States, for comparison. Extremely wealthy, advanced technology, excellent living standards\u2014horrible disparity. Japan is also a wealthy country in terms of assets, and there is far less disparity but only in comparison to the United States as the most extreme example of it. The shared experience of Japanese people is that of the poor. They live poorly. They behave as poor people behave. They\u2019re obsessed with ethnicity as status, with class, and they suffer for it. China has manifested a communist ideology within a capitalist system. They have rich and poor, but overall it\u2019s a country with a well managed lack of disparity. And it\u2019s amazing because it\u2019s so huge. China has a bigger population than all of Africa combined. It\u2019s a miracle of government. ",
