            "answer_text": "In certain areas, due to historical reasons. During the Qin dynasty, the first emperor sent a team of top herbalists, chemists, biologists , scientists , 500 young boys and girls with a large to Japan looking for the legendary medicine that would make him immortal. The boys and girls were sent to make sure the search could continue. They stayed in Japan and the work ethnics and determination passed on. Further, during Japan's invasion of China, they used healthy Chinese to conduct many biological and chemical tests. For example , the victims were infected with various diseases and they would monitor the changes until the subjects died. They would also torture subjects in different subjects and record in various parts of the body and so long a person could survive. So, Japanese had many empirical data from live human subjects that could not have been obtained in a civilized world!. The most notorious Japanese regiment who was responsible for this war crime was the 731 . They were never brought to justice. In fact, the Americans got the research results in return for turning a blind eye to the atrocity committed . Naturally, the Chinese don't have the research findings . In those areas China is behind. ",
